Package com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.collections

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockMap<V>
    A Map implementation for mapping values to Block Locations (offline Blocks)
    BlockSet
    A Set implementation for storing Block Locations (offline Blocks)
    ClassMap<V>
    A map that obtains the value bound to a given Class.
    CollectionBasics
    Provides basic implementations for various methods used in collections
    CollectionBasics.ListEntry<T>  
    EntityMap<K extends org.bukkit.entity.Entity,V>
    A HashMap that allows binding data to live entities without causing memory issues
    Entities are directly stored, when an entity is removed from the server it's binding is lost as well
    If you wish to map in a persistent way, use an identifier key (id, UUID, name) of an entity instead
    EntryList<K,V>
    A basic ArrayList implementation for storing entries
    FilteredCollection<E>
    A basic implementation of a Collection that filters some elements from a base Collection.
    FilteredCollectionSelf<E>
    A self-filtering FilteredCollection implementation.
    InstanceBuffer<E>
    Keeps instances of elements available even after clearing to avoid the creation of new instances.
    InterpolatedMap
    Uses a Double-Double sorted map system to linearly interpolate between values.
    List2D<E>
    A list implementation that uses a backing array of lists.
    List2DIterator<E>
    An iterator that can iterate over a collection of lists
    List2DListIterator<E>
    A List Iterator that can iterate over a collection of collections.
    StringMap<V>
    A String HashMap providing a few extra useful methods
    StringMapCaseInsensitive<V>
    A high-performance HashMap implementation that ignores the case of keys.
    UniqueList<E>
    A List implementation that only stores unique values, like a Set does
